heading: Sanctuary of Kalabsha (Elephantine, Egypt).
general-note: Here are entered works on a small Ptolemaic chapel that was built into the Roman Temple of Kalabsha and revealed when that structure was dismantled and that was reconstructed on Elephantine Island. Works on the temple built during Roman times at Kalabsha, Egypt, that was dismantled in 1962 and reassembled at a higher site south of the new Aswan Dam are entered under. Temple of Kalabsha (New Kalabsha, Egypt)..
